speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Hey!! We are so in luck! Treeger said that we could have all this cool stuff from the basement. Wait right there.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Oh no-no-no, I'm, I'm paddling away!

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Huh?!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Wow! Really?! We get all this rusty crap for free?!

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Uh-huh. This and a bunch of bubble wrap. And, some of it is not even popped!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Could we be more white trash?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: How desperate am I?

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Oh! Good thing Chandler's not here, he always wins at this game.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: I just told my Mom I'd cater a party for her.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: How come?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Because I need the money, and I thought that it'd be a great way to get rid of that last little schmidgen of self-respect.

transcript: Come on, I think this is a good thing. I don't think Mom would've hired you if she didn't think you were good at what you do.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: You don't have to stick up for her. She can't here you.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Hey! Umm, do you guys have any juice?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Just pickle.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Hey uh, Rach, funny story. I ah, bumped into Joanna on the street yesterday.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: My boss, Joanna? Wow, that must've been awkward.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Well, no, actually she uh, asked me if I wanted to get a drink.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: You ah, you didn't say 'Yes' to that did you?

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: No. No!

speaker: ['Joanna']
transcript: Hello, Rachel.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Well, not at first.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: What is she doing here?

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: I don't understand! Last time you went out with her you said she was a 'big, dull dud.'

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Well, I think I judged her too quickly, and this time we were able to take the relationship to the next level.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Well, last time I almost got fired. You must end it, you must end it now!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Oh, come on! It's not like this is an everyday occurrence for me! I mean usually I'm pretty much just in there by myself.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Chandler!! Promise me, you will end it.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: Okay, I promise, I'll end it.

speaker: ['Rachel Green']
transcript: Thank you.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: I hope you know what I'm giving up for ya, because she's not just the boss in your office, if you know what I mean.

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Yeah-eh-eah! Oh-oh, sorry, I-I knew what he meant.

speaker: ['Judy Geller']
transcript: How's the hired help?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Doing great, the quiches are coming along.

transcript: What's this? Blue nail polish?

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Yeah, I thought it was cute.

speaker: ['Judy Geller']
transcript: Ahh, that's what your Grandmother's hands looked like when we found her.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Let me ask you a question.

speaker: ['Judy Geller']
transcript: Hmm.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Why did you hire me?

speaker: ['Judy Geller']
transcript: Oh, well Richard raved about the food at his party, of course you were sleeping with him. Then I heard the food at that lesbian wedding was very nice, I assume you weren't sleeping with anybody there. Though, at least that would be something.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Oh my God! Did you hear that? She hired me because she thinks I'm good.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Okay, I didn't hear that.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Oh yeah, she didn't hire me out of pity, it wasn't so she could pick on me in front of her friends, she actually thinks I'm good.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Wow! And hey, it's cool if you're a lesbian!

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Good afternoon, are you the decision maker of the house?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Uhhhh.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Do you ah, currently own a set of encyclopedias?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: No! No. But ah, try the classifieds, people sell everything in there.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Actually, I'm not buying. I'm selling. Let me ask you one question. Do your friends ever have a conversation and you just nod along even though you're not really sure what they're talking about?

speaker: ['Ross Geller']
transcript: ...I'm telling you it's totally unconstituional.

speaker: ['Chandler Bing', 'Monica Geller', 'Phoebe Buffay', 'Rachel Green']
transcript: Oh yeah, I totally agree.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: ...I think he deserves a Nobel Prize.

speaker: ['#ALL#']
transcript: Nooo!!

speaker: ['Chandler Bing']
transcript: ...it was like the Algonquin kids table.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Excuse me, I'm sorry, you haven't said anything for about two and a half minutes, are you at all interested?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Yeah-well-yeah! Yeah-oh-yeah. Come on in.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: So, here's somebody interesting, Joey. What do you know about Van Gogh?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: He cut off his ear.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: And?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: I'm out.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: He painted that.

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Wow! That's pretty nice. I thought he cut off his ear 'cause he sucked. What else you got in there?

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Let's see, ahhh... Where does the Pope live?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: In the woods. No wait-wait, that's the joke answer.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: Actually its, Vatican City. Now ahh, what do you know about vulcanised rubber?

speaker: ['Joey Tribbiani']
transcript: Spock's birth control.

speaker: ['The Salesman']
transcript: You need these books.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Hey!

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Hi.

transcript: This used to be your room? Wow! You must've been in really good shape as a kid.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Ohh, I'm such an idiot. I can't believe I actually thought she could change.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Well, who cares what your Mom thinks? So you pulled a Monica.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: Oh good, I'm glad that's catching on.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: No but, why does that have to be a bad thing. Just change what it means. Y'know? Go down there and prove your Mother wrong. Finish the job you were hired to do, and we'll call that pulling a Monica.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: What?

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Okay, umm, if a kid gets straight A's, his parents would say, "Yeah, he pulled a Monica." Y'know? Or a fireman saves a baby, and they go, "Yeah I know, he pulled a Monica." Or someone hits a homerun and the announcer says, "Yeah, that one's outta here." Though some things don't change.

speaker: ['Monica Geller']
transcript: All right, I'll go down there. But, I'm not gonna serve the lasagna. I'm gonna serve something I make.

speaker: ['Phoebe Buffay']
transcript: Wow! My breasts are really strong.

transcript: Chandler! Chandler, please, I have to get you locked up back the way you were, I am sooo gonna lose my job, she's very private about her office. Now I know why.

transcript: Hey, look, you're in trouble either way! Okay? If she comes back and sees me locked to this instead of the chair, she's gonna know you were in here. So you might as well just let me go.

transcript: What if I clean your bathroom for a month?

transcript: Sophie sit!!

transcript: No! God, would you just calm down!

transcript: So, what do you say, Joey? You get the whole set of encyclopedias for twelve hundred dollars, which works out to just 50 bucks a book!

transcript: Twelve hundred dollars? You think I have $1200? I'm home in the middle of the day, and I got patio furniture in my living room. I guess there's a few things you don't get from book learnin'.
